# Portfolio HTML/CSS Standards

- Use semantic structure: `header`, `nav`, `main`, `section`, `article`.
- Keep navigation consistent: section `id` must match `href="#..."` links.
- Have exactly one `h1` per page; headings should follow a logical order.
- Prefer class-based styling; avoid inline styles.
- Define colors/spacings as CSS custom properties in `:root` and reuse via `var(...)`.
- Ensure accessibility: visible focus for `a`/`button` and meaningful link text.
- Keep responsive behavior via `@media` blocks (no layout-breaking fixed widths).

## Example (minimal)

```html
<header>...</header>
<main>
  <section id="about">...</section>
  <section id="projects">...</section>
</main>
```
